    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the creation of salts or esters of sulfuric acid that occurs when sulfate ions are incorporated into molecules. In a conservation science context sulfation most often refers to chemical weathering of stone by airborne pollution.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
